<TITLE> 7 burned as CNG cylinder catches fire </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Mar 19 (bdnews24.com)  Seven people sustained burns as fire erupted from a leaking gas cylinder of a bus at a garage in Chittagong on Friday. Gas leaking from a CNG cylinder of an under-repair bus caught fire at Shah Amanat Motor Workshop adjoining the city's Bahaddarhat bus terminal around 10am, Chandgaon police sub inspector Mohammed Sharif told bdnews24.com. Two other buses in the garage also caught fire, he said. The injured, including garage workers and a bus helper, were admitted to Chittagong Medical Hospital. "The condition of one is critical," Mohammed Khaled, duty doctor of the CMCH burns unit, said. Bishu Das, a fire fighter of the Agrabad Fire Brigade, said the three buses and garage equipment were gutted in the fire. bdne
